<item>
            <title>[ISS-140] Refactoring: Investigate Use of external template engine</title>
                <link>http://jira.perfect.org:8080/browse/ISS-140</link>
                <project id="10007" key="ISS">Issues</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I suggest that the template engine should be decoupled from the framework. We can use a default template engine, loading it as a submodule. That way a developer will have the ability to use the template engine of her choice with a little configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would prefer depending on an external template engine. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/groue/GRMustache.swift&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;GRMustache&lt;/a&gt; appears that is closer to our own mustache template engine and it would be a good replacement candidate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also feel that the following features should investigated:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] Route gluing a Handler/Controller? with a Template&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] template extensions&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] template partial support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
